{
  "texts": [
    "We envision GABE as a systematic, bottom-up methodology that deploys micro-level autonomous AI agents in controlled settings, where they are given opportunities to interact organically with each other.",
    "These interactions can produce emergent behaviors that are not presumed by the researcher from the outset and are unknown to the individual LLMs.",
    "Throughout the simulations, the decisions, rationales, and outcomes of each AI agent are meticulously tracked, enabling an in-depth study of strategic interactions.",
    "In this sense, GABE has much in common with more traditional simulation methods (Davis et al., 2007), but it harnesses the power of generative AI to mimic actual human behavior.",
    "Because these experiments are conducted completely in silico, some computational infrastructure is required."
  ]
}